Wawrzyniec Jerzy Żuławski (14 February 1916, in Zakopane – 18 August 1957, in the Alps), also known as Wawa, was a Polish alpinist, educator, composer, music critic, and musicologist.
Żuławski published music reviews in Ruch Muzyczny, Express Wieczorny, Nowa Kultura.
He died on Mont Blanc during a rescue action in 1957.
Wierchowe nuty, vocal compositions for choir and violin solo, 1955
